    "role": "instrument",
    "bullets": [
      "Chinese A-share listed firms from 2007 to 2024, relating the visual aesthetics of annual reports to future stock price crash risk.",
      "A multimodal large language model, not named, is applied to annual reports to construct an aesthetics measure; no validation against ground truth is reported.",
      "Firms with highly aesthetic annual reports have significantly lower future crash risk, robust to endogeneity tests, with effects stronger under higher technological complexity and lower default risk."
    ],
